uFerris Hardware and Software Open-Source License
=================================================

OVERVIEW
--------
This repository contains the uFerris family of open-source hardware designs
and software tools developed to support learning and experimentation with
embedded Rust. It includes multiple derivative boards and compatible firmware.

Unless otherwise noted, all files in this repository are covered by the
licenses described below.

------------------------------------------------------------
HARDWARE LICENSE — Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International
------------------------------------------------------------
The hardware design files (schematics, PCB layouts, BOMs, 3D models, and other
related design assets) for all uFerris boards and their derivatives are licensed
under the Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International License
(CC BY-SA 4.0).

You are free to:
- **Share** — copy and redistribute the material in any medium or format
- **Adapt** — remix, transform, and build upon the material for any purpose,
  including commercial use.

Under the following terms:
- **Attribution** — You must give appropriate credit, provide a link to the
  license, and indicate if changes were made.
- **ShareAlike** — If you remix, transform, or build upon the material, you must
  distribute your contributions under the same license as the original.

Full license text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

This applies to all board revisions, derivative designs, and hardware variants
contained in this repository (e.g., boards supporting different Seeed Studio
Xiao modules or other MCU pinouts derived from the uFerris base design).

